Over forty-five million Americans suffer from habitual, recurring headaches. This is more than the number of Americans with heart disease, asthma, or diabetes. In fact, at any one time, an estimated twenty million Americans are experiencing a headache.

Yet, the cause of headaches remains a mystery. This interesting and fact-filled book examines the mystery that surrounds headaches, as well as traditional and alternative headache treatments, the challenges of living with headaches, and the direction of future research.
